To center the two article divs horizontally, you can use Flexbox or Grid in your CSS. Here’s how you can do it with both methods:

### Using Flexbox

1. **Add a container around the articles:**
   ```html
   <div class="article-container">
     <div class="article">Article 1</div>
     <div class="article">Article 2</div>
   </div>
   ```

2. **Style the container with Flexbox:**
   ```css
   .article-container {
     display: flex;
     justify-content: center;
   }

   .article {
     /* Your existing styles */
   }
   ```

### Using Grid

1. **Add a container around the articles:**
   ```html
   <div class="article-container">
     <div class="article">Article 1</div>
     <div class="article">Article 2</div>
   </div>
   ```

2. **Style the container with Grid:**
   ```css
   .article-container {
     display: grid;
     justify-items: center;
   }

   .article {
     /* Your existing styles */
   }
   ```

Both methods will center the articles horizontally within their container. Choose the one that best fits your layout and design needs.

